description: From Latin amphisbaena, from Ancient Greek ἀμφίσβαινα (amphísbaina), from ἀμφίς (amphís, “both ways”) +‎ βαίνω (baínō, “I go”).

entries.meaning: (mythology) A mythical serpent having a head at each end of its body, able to move in either direction.
A member of a genus of lizards, native to the Americas, having extremities which are very similar.
